<para>
  This command sets the size of the buffer used to store old sets of
  <link linkend="Section-Concepts-Pin">pinned nodes</link> in a
  &skel;.  The buffer enables the <link
  linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Skeleton.PinNodes.Undo"><command>Undo</command></link>
  and <link
  linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Skeleton.PinNodes.Redo"><command>Redo</command></link>
  commands in the node pinning menu.  Using a larger buffer size will
  use more memory but enable more operations to be undone.
</para>
<warning>
  <para>
    Reducing the buffer size can cause data loss.
  </para>
</warning>

